  "_comment": "Source of truth for /book/ widgets. The first block of entries mirrors the published cities on https://book.usesession.com/i/pN8nwzWsHa (Now Booking grid), and the remaining entries are the Coming Soon roadmap. Coming Soon is sorted soonest-first within its block. Sold-out math: 1-day cap=21, 2-day cap=42 (the 30/60 raw Session capacity includes 9/18 reserves we never expose). Status: now_open | sold_out (Use Session published) | opening_soon (date locked, not yet on sale) | scheduling (month known, weekend TBD). spotsLeft drives the urgency badge if < 10. Coming Soon entries intentionally leave `weekend` blank — the widget no longer surfaces the month/year to visitors so distant cities don't feel 'too far' and bounce; weekendStart is kept internally so the Opens Soon pill still highlights the soonest month. Coming Soon is also intentionally trimmed to the next ~16 cities (full Aug block + 4 hand-picked Sep cities) — surfacing the entire 4-month roadmap (a) overwhelms casual visitors, (b) hands competitors a free deployment schedule, and (c) dilutes the urgency cue (when half the list glows, none of it feels urgent). The full pipeline still lives in Jonathan's Schedule tab; we just don't publish it. The widget adds a '+N more cities' footer line and shuffles row order within each month so the deployment sequence isn't leaked. Last synced 2026-05-28. Summit NJ and Ridgewood NJ Jun are hidden per Jonathan (not on Use Session public index). 9 published cities in the Now Booking block (4 sold out, 5 open); 12 Aug + 4 Sep cities in Coming Soon (~30 more cities tracked internally for Sep through Nov).",
